SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Secretary of State Shenna Bellows state
 ment on federal court striking down provisions of anti-voting Executive Or
 der
DESCRIPTION:Secretary of State Shenna Bellows statement on federal court s
 triking down provisions of anti-voting Executive Order \n<span><span lang=
 "lang">jana.spaulding…</span></span>\n\n<span><time datetime="2026-06-24
 T16:28:30-04:00" title="Wednesday\, June 24\, 2026 - 16:28">Wed\, 06/24/20
 26 - 16:28</time>\n</span>\n\n          <p><time datetime="2026-06-24T12:0
 0:00Z">6/24/2026</time>\n</p>\n    \n  <div>\n                  <div>\n   
        <p><strong>AUGUSTA\, MAINE</strong> – Secretary of State Shenna 
 Bellows issued the following statement in response to Chief U.S. District 
 Judge Denise Casper permanently enjoining provisions of a 2025 anti-voting
  Executive Order by President Trump. </p><p>“Donald Trump continues to 
 stack up loss after loss in court\, and as we are now just days away from 
 the 250<sup>th</sup> anniversary of the birth of our nation\, states conti
 nue to show that when we stand united\, we can successfully defend the rul
 e of law and our rights to administer elections. </p><p>The judge could n
 ot have stated it more plainly – the U.S. Constitution assigns control o
 ver elections to the States and does not grant the president any powers ov
 er elections. We will continue to fight Donald Trump and the DOJ’s every
  attempt to interfere with free and fair elections.”</p><p>The ruling co
 mes in response to a 19-state litigation challenging the order and stated\
 , “there is no evidence in this record of widespread “illegal voting\,
  discrimination\, fraud\, and other forms of malfeasance and error” with
 in American elections\, which the Executive Order purports to safeguard ag
 ainst.”</p><p class="text-align-center">### </p><p><strong>Attachment:<
 /strong> <a href="https://www.maine.gov/sos/sites/maine.gov.sos/files/inli
 ne-files/2026-06-24%20-%20MSJ%20Mem.%20and%20Order.pdf" title="2026-06-24 
 - MSJ Mem. and Order.pdf">Memorandum and Order</a></p>\n        </div>\n  
           </div>\nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/secretary-state-shenna-be
 llows-statement-federal-court-striking-down-provisions-anti-voting
URL:https://www.maine.gov/sos/news/secretary-state-shenna-bellows-statemen
 t-federal-court-striking-down-provisions-anti-voting
CATEGORIES:Maine Secretary of State
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
