SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces additional races for Ranked Choice Voting tabulations\, recounts
DESCRIPTION:Maine Secretary of State’s Office announces additional races
  for Ranked Choice Voting tabulations\, recounts\n<span><span lang="lang">
 jana.spaulding…</span></span>\n\n<span><time datetime="2026-06-16T08:59:
 02-04:00" title="Tuesday\, June 16\, 2026 - 08:59">Tue\, 06/16/2026 - 08:5
 9</time>\n</span>\n\n          <p><time datetime="2026-06-16T12:00:00Z">6/
 16/2026</time>\n</p>\n    \n  <div>\n                  <div>\n          <p
 ><strong>AUGUSTA\, MAINE</strong> – The Department of the Secretary of S
 tate announced today two additional races will proceed to ranked choice vo
 ting tabulation and three to recounts:</p><p>Ranked choice tabulation:</p>
 <ul><li>House District 58 – Republican (Belgrade\, Fayette\, Rome\, Vien
 na\, Mount Vernon\, New Sharon)</li><li>Senate District 4 – Republican (
 Bradford\; Charleston\, Corinna\, Corinth\, Dexter\, Exeter\, Garland\, Gl
 enburn\, Hudson\, Kenduskeag\, Levant)</li><li>Governor – Democrat</li><
 li>Governor – Republican </li><li>U.S. Congress CD2 – Democrat </li>
 </ul><p>Recounts:</p><ul><li>Senate District 30 – Democrat (Gorham\, Sca
 rborough (part))</li><li>House District 49 – Republican (Arrowsic\, Geor
 getown\, Phippsburg\, West Bath\, Woolwich)</li><li>House District 135 –
  Democrat  (Kennebunk (part))</li></ul><p>The ranked choice tabulation pr
 ocess began on Friday\, June 12 at 1 PM at the Maine Department of Public 
 Safety Headquarters building located at 45 Commerce Drive in Augusta and i
 s expected to conclude this week. The ranked choice process is open to the
  public and media and is being livestreamed on the Secretary of State’s
  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@mesecofstate">YouTube page</a>. Recoun
 ts will begin next week with dates to be announced later this week.</p><p>
 <strong>How Ranked Choice Voting works in Maine:</strong> In Ranked Choice
  Voting races\, a candidate must receive more than 50% of the first-choice
  votes as counted on Election Day to win the race outright. If no candidat
 e appears to have achieved this based on initial unofficial results report
 s from \nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-office-anno
 unces-additional-races-ranked-choice-voting-tabulations
URL:https://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-office-announces
 -additional-races-ranked-choice-voting-tabulations
