SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces recount schedule
DESCRIPTION:Maine Secretary of State’s Office announces recount schedule
 \n<span><span lang="lang">jana.spaulding…</span></span>\n\n<span><time d
 atetime="2026-06-16T12:13:27-04:00" title="Tuesday\, June 16\, 2026 - 12:1
 3">Tue\, 06/16/2026 - 12:13</time>\n</span>\n\n          <p><time datetime
 ="2026-06-16T12:00:00Z">6/16/2026</time>\n</p>\n    \n  <div>\n           
        <div>\n          <p><strong>AUGUSTA\, MAINE</strong> – The Depart
 ment of the Secretary of State announced the schedule for recounts request
 ed by candidates in three races:</p><p>Recounts:</p><ul><li>Monday\, June 
 22 at 9 a.m.: Senate District 30 – Democrat </li><li>Thursday\, June 25
  at 9 a.m.: House District 49 – Republican</li><li>Thursday\, June 25 at
  1 p.m.: House District 135 – Democrat  </li></ul><p>The recounts will
  take place in the Florian Room located at the Maine Public Safety Buildin
 g at 45 Commerce Ave.\, Augusta. Recounts are open to the public and media
  and will be livestreamed on the Secretary of State’s <a href="https://
 www.youtube.com/@mesecofstate">YouTube page</a>.</p><p>Additional recounts
  could be requested following the conclusion of the ranked choice voting t
 abulations.</p><p><strong>Recount process:</strong> Maine statute <a href
 ="https://legislature.maine.gov/legis/statutes/21-A/title21-Asec737-A.html
 " title="Link to statute language">Title 21-A\, §737-A</a> lays out a sp
 ecific plan\, process and any related costs for votes to be recounted. In 
 a recount\, representatives of each candidate and staff members from the D
 epartment of the Secretary of State manually review each paper ballot to d
 etermine the official vote tally:</p><ul><li><strong>In Ranked Choice Voti
 ng races</strong>: only a candidate who received one of the top three rank
 ings at the end of the penultimate round of ranked‑choice counting may r
 equest a recount\, and they must file with the Secretary of State a writte
 n request within five business days after results are announced.  </li><
 li><strong>In non-Ranked Choice races: </strong>any candidate \nhttps://w
 ww.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-office-announces-recount-sche
 dule
