SUMMARY:[Governor / Executive Branch] 211 Maine Day - July 7
DESCRIPTION:211 Maine Day - July 7\n            <div><p><strong>WHEREAS</s
 trong>\, 211 Maine is a Maine-based health and human services and emergenc
 y preparedness and response helpline\, providing free and confidential ref
 errals to needed resources to Maine people\; and</p><p><strong>WHEREAS</st
 rong>\, 211 Maine provides 24/7 service statewide by people employed in Ma
 ine through efficient and effective response to the growing complexities a
 nd needs of Maine residents\; and</p><p><strong>WHEREAS</strong>\, for 20 
 years\, 211 Maine has worked diligently to confront and reduce the stigma 
 associated with seeking support by affirming that doing so reflects person
 al strength\; and</p><p><strong>WHEREAS</strong>\, since 2006\, 211 Maine 
 specialists have answered more than 1 million calls from people across the
  state looking for needed information from housing support and food resour
 ces to substance use and recovery services\; and</p><p><strong>WHEREAS</st
 rong>\, 211 Maine provides emergency operations support during times of na
 tural and other disasters\, including assisting the Maine Emergency Manage
 ment Agency field calls from those impacted and collecting data to inform 
 severity and locations of need\, and directing people looking for local he
 ating shelters or cooling centers\; and</p><p><strong>WHEREAS</strong>\, 2
 11 Maine handles several specialized services and partnerships\, including
  providing the Opiate Helpline and the Gambling Helpline\, distributing em
 ergency heating assistance through the Keep Me Warm fund\, and serving as 
 a resource for mental health services and tax preparation\; and</p><p><str
 ong>WHEREAS</strong>\, 211 Maine stands as a compelling example of how coo
 rdinated efforts among government\, nonprofit organizations\, and private-
 sector partners can elevate the well-being of Maine's citizens\; </p><p><
 strong>NOW THEREFORE</strong>\, be it resolved that I\, Janet T. Mills\, G
 overnor of the State of Maine\, do hereby proclaim July 7\, 2026 as</p><h2
  class="text-align-center">211 Maine Day</h2>\nhttp://www.maine.gov/govern
 or/mills/official_documents/proclamations/2026-06-211-maine-day-july-7
URL:http://www.maine.gov/governor/mills/official_documents/proclamations/2
 026-06-211-maine-day-july-7
CATEGORIES:Governor / Executive Branch
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
